headline: Home Builders Rise. Lower Mortgage Rates Could Be Here to Stay.
summary: Shares of home builders were climbing after the Federal Reserve’s decision Wednesday.  The iShares U.S. Home Construction ETF, which tracks builders and related companies, was up 1% shortly after the central bank voted to cut rates.  Three of the nation’s largest builders, D.R. Horton, Lennar, and PulteGroup, were up 1.1%, 1.4%, and 1.3%, respectively.

headline: Is Builder Confidence Set to Rebound on Looming Fed Rate Cuts?
summary: Builder confidence stayed flat in September, but falling mortgage rates may spark a housing market rebound, with stocks like DHI, TOL, HD, LOW and MAS already gaining ground.
